H0.text: Cell -> organ -> tissue -> organ system is the sequence that identifies the levels of organization of body structures in a human from simplest to most complex.

H1.text: Organ system → cell → tissue → organ is the sequence that identifies the levels of organization of body structures in a human from simplest to most complex.

H2.text: Tissue -> organ -> organ system -> cell is the sequence that identifies the levels of organization of body structures in a human from simplest to most complex.

H3.text: Cell → tissue → organ → organ system is the sequence that identifies the levels of organization of body structures in a human from simplest to most complex.

A4.text: It is composed of many different types of cells that together create tissues and subsequently organs and then organ systems.
